10 Rules of Good Studying
========================================================

```{r, echo=FALSE}
library(RColorBrewer)
library(wordcloud)
library(tm)

colors1 <- brewer.pal(9, "Greens")
palette1 <- colorRampPalette(colors1)
colors2 <- brewer.pal(9, "YlOrRd")
palette2 <- colorRampPalette(colors2)

datasetInput <- data.frame(
        Name = c("Recall",
                 "Test",
                 "Chunk",
                 "Space",
                 "Alternate Techniques",
                 "Breaks",
                 "Analogies",
                 "Focus",
                 "Frogs First",
                 "Mental Contrast"),
        Value = c(5,8,6,5,3,5,6,9,3,3), stringsAsFactors=FALSE)

wordcloud(datasetInput$Name, datasetInput$Value, scale=c(8,1), 
          max.words=100, random.order=TRUE, random.color=FALSE,
          rot.per=0.5, use.r.layout=FALSE, colors=rainbow(10))
```

Ten Rules of Good Studying
========================================================
1. Use recall
- Test yourself
- Chunk your problems
- Space your repetition
- Alternate different problem-solving techniques during your practice
- Take breaks
- Use explanatory questioning and simple analogies
- Focus
- Eat your frogs first
- Make a mental contrast

